cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.GT, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with cache-enabled cellular networks and device-to-device communication, which are both networking concepts. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the average ergodic rate of an arbitrary user requesting a particular content, which is a concept related to information theory. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the selection of D2D helpers and the trade-off between performance metrics, which are concepts related to social and information networks. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper discusses the selection of D2D helpers and the trade-off between performance metrics, which are concepts related to game theory. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with content availability and the distribution of content, which are concepts related to multimedia.
